name: Tree Runners
description: Say what you will about Allbirds, but the brand's bouncy, breathable Allbirds help your feet stay cool all summer long. Plus, they’re machine washable and you can wear ‘em sockless. A perfect formula for a summer shoe.

name: Killshot OG Sneaker
description: It was only a few years ago that it was nearly impossible to get your hands on the Nike Killshot 2, a low-slung sneaker that launched (what felt like) a billion blogs and had a nasty habit of selling out every time it released. Now, you can snatch it up with a little less hassle. And that's great. But the real flex? Don't opt for the sequel. Go with the OG version, which is a little sportier, a little more throwback in feel, and entirely right for the summer ahead.

name: Desert Boot Sand Suede
description: The only boots you need when the weather gets warm. And just plain some of the best boots out there, period.

name: Lace-Up Beach Sneaker
description: Basic, comfy sneakers you can wear into the ground, whether it's on a hot city street, countryside, or, if its name means anything, the beach.

name: Original Achilles Leather Sneakers
description: Common Projects' cool-guy, high-end sneakers are officially a modern-day icon. And if you've got the scratch, they'll make a truly investment-worthy addition to your portfolio.

name: Arizona Essentials EVA
description: Wear 'em around your house. Wear 'em to the beach. Wear 'em as you wade in the ocean (they're waterproof!). Wear 'em with socks, even. They're so damn comfortable, you'll want to explore all your options.

name: Old Skool Sneakers
description: If you want to fully embrace that laid-back, warm-weather vibe, go with a pair of sneakers worn by every California surfer and skater since the dawn of time (or since Vans first started making them).

name: Club C 85 Sneakers
description: The Club C. Inspired by old-school tennis style, and yet perfectly suited to right now.

name: Chuck 70 High-Top Sneaker
description: There's just something about that fresh pair of Chucks feeling.

name: Stan Smith Sneakers
description: The Stan Smith stays winning, especially in this new iteration made from a material that's at least 50 percent recycled plastic but feels just like leather.

name: Edge Leather Slip-On
description: Canvas is well and good, but luxe Italian leather is exactly what you need to take your go-to summer slip-ons to an effortlessly elevated place.
